==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Headland
<hw>Head"land</hw> <pr>(h⟦ecr⟧d"l⟦acr⟧nd)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A cape; a promontory; a point of land projecting into
the sea or other expanse of water.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Sow the
<xex>headland</xex> with wheat.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A ridge or strip of unplowed at the ends of furrows,
or near a fence.</def> <rj><au>Tusser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Headless</ent>⟦br⟧
